\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 3/14/2026}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There is a little less than week left until we see each other again. When we meet on the 19th-22nd, I will draw the drawing that is stapled to this letter. I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92m putting it off until then to be efficient with my time :). Gotta finish up this book!}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Gotta finish it up because it needs to be done. I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve stressed about it a little bit. It\u8217\'92s part of suite of stresses that we might call \u8216\'91anxious about the future\u8217\'92. This anxiety is caused by a mild catastrophizing that I do. I think, you know, no fucking way this book is worth anything, and so of course it\u8217\'92s a waste of time. It becomes a self-fulfilling thought because I become less eager to work on it, less invested, less interested, and no uninterested writer has ever written anything interesting.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 All that bullshit thinking about the future is what I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve been avoiding these past few years.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Turn catastrophising against itself. Because what if what I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92m feeling for you is the best feeling any human being has ever had, and I\u8217\'92m not dwelling in it it because I\u8217\'92m worried about income, or asymmetry, or some other bullshit. It would be a catastrophe for all of humanity if I did not dwell in these feelings. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You may be thinking that catastrophising about catastrophising is not a sustainable strategy, but it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s all good because these thoughts lead me into thinking about loving you. I think about holding you in the shower, and telling you I love you, and you smiling, and me kissing that smile, and then my whole body sort of crunches up like I\u8217\'92ve just been shot by cupid\u8217\'92s arrow.}}